Geisha

Target IP: 192.168.186.82

Scanning


This target host has seven TCP ports open. The FTP application does not allow anonymous login. Therefore, I will start enumeration with the other HTTP applications.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application. The source-code of this page does not provide anything useful. A file info.php can be accessed, but this PHP file contains contains the number 1 inside it.

Port 7125: HTTP

This port displays the same webpage as port 80. However, doing a directory search shows interesting information. The /passwd files the /etc/passwd file. This file shows a username called geisha exists on the target machine.

Port 21: FTP

From the /passwd fiile, I obtained a username called geisha. Performing a bruteforce against FTP using rockyou.txt worked. I obtained the geisha:letmein login details.


Using the credentials, I downloaded all the files on my machine. The local.txt flag file is here. I did not find anything important here.

Exploitation


Reusing the password letmein worked with geisha for SSH. Now I have a foothold on the machine as geisha.

Privilege Escalation


Looks like /usr/bin/base32 binary can be used to read the root's proof.txt flag file.

Flags


The proof.txt and local.txt flag file contents.
